# Honeypot Monitor CLI

A terminal-based monitoring application for Kippo honeypot traffic analysis.

## Project Structure

```
honeypot-monitor-cli/
├── src/
│   └── honeypot_monitor/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       ├── main.py                 # Main application entry point
│       ├── interfaces/             # Abstract base classes and interfaces
│       │   ├── __init__.py
│       │   ├── log_parser_interface.py
│       │   ├── monitor_interface.py
│       │   ├── analyzer_interface.py
│       │   └── notifier_interface.py
│       ├── models/                 # Data models
│       │   ├── __init__.py
│       │   ├── log_entry.py
│       │   ├── session.py
│       │   ├── threat_assessment.py
│       │   └── irc_alert.py
│       ├── services/               # Business logic services
│       │   ├── __init__.py
│       │   ├── log_monitor.py
│       │   ├── log_parser.py
│       │   ├── threat_analyzer.py
│       │   └── irc_notifier.py
│       ├── tui/                    # Terminal UI components
│       │   ├── __init__.py
│       │   ├── main_app.py
│       │   ├── dashboard.py
│       │   ├── log_viewer.py
│       │   └── analysis_panel.py
│       └── config/                 # Configuration management
│           ├── __init__.py
│           ├── config_manager.py
│           └── settings.py
├── config/
│   └── default.yaml               # Default configuration
├── tests/                         # Test suite
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── test_models/
│   ├── test_services/
│   ├── test_tui/
│   └── test_config/
├── requirements.txt               # Python dependencies
├── setup.py                      # Package installation script
└── README.md                     # This file
```

## Installation

```bash
# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Install the package in development mode
pip install -e .
```

## Usage

```bash
# Run the application
honeypot-monitor

# Run with custom config
honeypot-monitor --config /path/to/config.yaml

# Override log path
honeypot-monitor --log-path /path/to/kippo.log
```

## Development Status

This project is currently in development. The basic project structure and interfaces have been established. Individual components will be implemented according to the task list in the specification.

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- textual (TUI framework)
- watchdog (file monitoring)
- PyYAML (configuration)
- irc (IRC notifications)

